dismissalText.commentary: Nathan Astle run out (Streak) 67 (89b 8x4 2x6 105m) SR: 75.28

notes: The dismissal of GJ Whittall brought up 100 ODI wickets for CZ Harris, the 6th New Zealander to reach that mark.

SB O'Connor 5-39 is his best bowling figures in ODIs (previous: 4-51 v Australia at Sydney in 1997-98) and the the best bowling figures by a New Zealander v Zimbabwe (previous: DL Vettori 4-49 at Hamilton in 1997-98).
The 2nd wicket partnership of 103 between NJ Astle and AC Parore is a new record for New Zealand v Zimbabwe (previous: 87 by RT Latham and AH Jones at Bulawayo in 1992-93).

milestones.description: Heath Streak has become the top wicket-taker for ZIM in ODIs with 60 wickets, going past Eddo Brandes's 59
